- drift_by_domain (simula, tb, arabic, regulations)
- drift_by_type (DRIFT-001 through DRIFT-008)
- false_positive_rate (manual review feedback)
- blocked_prs_count (per week)
- exceptions_active (current count)
- exceptions_expired (needing cleanup)

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# COMPLETION STANDARD
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

The spec-drift auditor is correct when:
- No specification can drift from implementation without detection
- No schema can diverge from spec without warning
- No code can contradict spec requirements without blocking
- All drift is tracked, evidenced, and remediated
- Audit history is preserved for compliance review

